sh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"8ea33dfeb9c126351595da0f06a60bbd746b75a45756465bda0cf517cc2cceb6","event_uuid":"a83d66d5-10a3-429e-b3b6-86c3098ec6ef","position":{"commit_sha":"bd258f3fe3c76be5f299e6d16e80b0fbd76a661b","position":"1784487072463640001-a83d66d5-10a3-429e-b3b6-86c3098ec6ef"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"9f4b65279949a6896188ea0c6e6d3d05a17624a360f7383b42d275c16532ff0e","event_uuid":"c8b5ed6b-e698-44f4-b0aa-58621cecda1a","position":{"commit_sha":"7b4f63c74f7c2a1cd735d011ac114a0f459b0ae6","position":"1784487523152410842-c8b5ed6b-e698-44f4-b0aa-58621cecda1a"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-215_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"5e1736fd-6a46-425f-96e3-3460f9fcb4f7","comments":[],"created_at":1784249113155451001,"creation_channel":"unknown","deps":[{"link_uuid":"932c70fb-a58b-473f-82ed-84c76a0ab790","relation":"discovered_from","target_id":"79da-c7e4-8d7c-471d"}],"description":"## Reproduction Steps\n1. Create ~/.config/rebar/config.toml (any content).\n2. `make test` (or run tests/unit/test_config_show.py::test_config_cli_json_output, ::test_sources_all_default_when_no_config, tests/unit/test_config_perf.py::test_deep_tree_walk_is_bounded).\n3. They FAIL (e.g. asserts user_config['exists'] is False, but it is True) because they read the real ~/.config/rebar/config.toml.\n\n## Root cause\nconftest _isolate_user_config sets XDG_CONFIG_HOME to an empty per-test dir, and config.user_config_path() honors it (verified: returns the empty-dir path). Yet these 3 tests still detect the host user config — likely a config-cache populated before the fixture applies, or a path these tests resolve outside the XDG-scoped seam. Surfaced by epic dc09 (79da provisions a machine-wide ~/.config/rebar/config.toml for signing), which makes these fail on any dev machine with a user config. Passes on CI (no user config) — not a code regression.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] The 3 tests pass with a real ~/.config/rebar/config.toml present (robust isolation — clear the config cache per test, or scope the read through the XDG-isolated path).\n- [ ] `make test` is green on a machine that has ~/.config/rebar/config.toml.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[],"parent_id":null,"parent_status_uuid":"6829d423-e987-4f84-a232-d765a30c6ab0","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":[],"ticket_id":"d716-3bce-7a95-4549","ticket_type":"bug","title":"config-show/perf tests leak the developer's ~/.config/rebar/config.toml despite XDG isolation (3 tests fail when a real user config exists)","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["1d6e651d-e924-4e5f-8ded-de1e4ad2bfcc","932c70fb-a58b-473f-82ed-84c76a0ab790","6829d423-e987-4f84-a232-d765a30c6ab0","a83d66d5-10a3-429e-b3b6-86c3098ec6ef","c8b5ed6b-e698-44f4-b0aa-58621cecda1a"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784487523152410843,"uuid":"fe1d676e-c3c7-4f52-8f8d-27424d9a9f43"}